You put MX records out like

	ms.uky.edu.	IN	MX	0 s.ms.uky.edu.
	ms.uky.edu.	IN	MX	1 e.ms.uky.edu.
	ms.uky.edu.	IN	MX	2 g.ms.uky.edu.

then play tricks in your mail system to make it recognize "ms.uky.edu"
as another name for the local machine.

I've been doing this for a couple of years in our MMDF configuration.

